wer":{"text":"Yes, Photoshop on mobile is a free mobile version of Photoshop with premium features that are available when you purchase a subscription. Add and remove objects, make targeted adjustments, collage and blend images, and more — all on your phone. To download the app, visit the app store on your device. You can start a free trial of Photoshop to try the full desktop app.","@type":"Answer"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"\n      \n        Is there a free online version of Photoshop?\n      \n    ","acceptedAnswer":{"text":"There isn’t a free version of Photoshop on the web, however you can try out some of Photoshop’s most popular tools and uses online with the help of guided tutorials without creating an Adobe account. To upload and edit your own photos, you’ll have to sign up for a Photoshop plan or start a free trial.","@type":"Answer"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"\n      \n        Is there student pricing for Photoshop?\n      \n    ","acceptedAnswer":{"text":"Yes, students and teachers save over 71% on the Creative Cloud Pro plan. Find out more here.","@type":"Answer"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"\n      \n        Are there generative AI features in Photoshop?\n      \n    ","acceptedAnswer":{"text":"Generative AI features like Generative Fill and Generative Expand are natively integrated into Photoshop, combining the power of AI with the precision of Photoshop, so you can create more with complete control. Add, expand, and remove content in images using features powered by Adobe Firefly, and then adjust them using the AI photo editing tools in Photoshop.","@type":"Answer"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"\n      \n        What are the steps to install the Photoshop (beta) app with new generative AI features?\n      \n    ","acceptedAnswer":{"text":"Get detailed installation instructions here.","@type":"Answer"}}]]}</script><link rel="stylesheet" href="/libs/styles/rounded-corners.css"><link rel="stylesheet" href="https://prod.adobeccstatic.com/unav/1.5/U